{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0eb0650d-5b2b-4b1f-9dcd-79da4eaf9dbc","content":"In MSTest 3.8.2, you get constructor injection for `TestContext` plus `async Task` support on `[TestInitialize]`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _httpClient = null!;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Asynchronous init via [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _httpClient = new HttpClient();\n        await _httpClient.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Initialization complete\");\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public void Cleanup()\n    {\n        _httpClient?.Dispose();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task AsyncTest()\n    {\n        var response = await _httpClient.GetAsync(\"https://example.com\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(response.IsSuccessStatusCode);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — inject `TestContext` directly; use for synchronous setup (field assignments, config).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — return `async Task` for any async work (DB connections, HTTP calls). Runs before each test.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** / **`[ClassCleanup]`** — available for one-time class-level setup if needed (must be `static`).\n- The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred in v3+.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6b36d1f3-7932-41ae-ad85-dbdfa7c5c9ce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), you can use constructor injection for `TestContext`. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended approach is:\n1. Constructor injection for `TestContext` (instead of the old property-based approach)\n2. `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` for class-level setup\n3. `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` for test-level setup\n4. For async initialization, MSTest 3.x supports `async Task` versions of `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]`\n\n\n5. You can combine constructor injection with async `[TestInitialize]` methods to handle both synchronous and asynchronous setup needs.","outputTokens":699,"requestId":"E447:9D49C:3E5A4DC:44856D2:6A02FB74"},"id":"977634a9-a42a-4072-8869-0086b1e5957a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:05:58.572Z","parentId":"78ce4d88-0833-4f1e-9016-cf77a1526d5d"}
